# The `ape update` verification fixtures are byte-exact: the release signature
# covers the SHA-256 of ape_checksums.txt, and the Sigstore bundle embeds that
# digest. A line-ending conversion (e.g. a Windows autocrlf checkout rewriting
# LF -> CRLF) would change the bytes and break the offline cosign-verify tests.
# Treat them as binary so git never touches their contents.
internal/apecmd/testdata/update/** -text
internal/apecmd/trusted_root.json -text
